1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Let's explore the Site Editor, which will allow you to design everything on your site

2
00:00:05,400 --> 00:00:08,400
using blocks, from the header to the footer and everything in between.

3
00:00:10,360 --> 00:00:13,360
Let's make our way to Appearance and click on Editor.

4
00:00:14,520 --> 00:00:17,520
This will open the Site Editor.

5
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:20,040
On the left there's the site view sidebar, and this nifty tool lets you dive into the

6
00:00:21,840 --> 00:00:24,840
key parts of your site, navigation, styles, pages, templates and patterns.

7
00:00:28,960 --> 00:00:31,960
This tutorial aims to gain a deep understanding of these elements.

8
00:00:33,840 --> 00:00:36,840
Let's start at the top with navigation.

9
00:00:37,080 --> 00:00:40,080
Here you can quickly see and tweak all your menus.

10
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:43,040
It's your command center for menu management.

11
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:45,920
You can make simple edits directly.

12
00:00:46,800 --> 00:00:49,800
Like Reordering.

13
00:00:53,040 --> 00:00:56,040
And when you click on the three vertical dots next to the name of the menu item, you can

14
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:00,000
rename, duplicate and delete the menu item as required.

15
00:01:02,760 --> 00:01:05,760
If opened in the editing mode, you can make certain changes without any distractions.

16
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:11,160
And updates will sync across your site.

17
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:13,800
When you click on the plus icon, you can add new pages or other menu items.

18
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:21,800
You will notice that the Navigation block is locked in this area.

19
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:25,640
If you would like to style your navigation menu, you will need to open a template or

20
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:29,480
the template part it is part of.

21
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:32,640
Next, let's talk about styles.

22
00:01:32,440 --> 00:01:35,440
When you select Styles, you will be able to browse through a variety of different style

23
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:40,440
combinations that come with your theme.

24
00:01:40,720 --> 00:01:43,720
When you click on Edit Styles, you can browse your styles from here and then change your

25
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:49,200
site's typography, colors and layout.

26
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:52,320
Let's see how it works.

27
00:01:50,960 --> 00:01:53,960
When you click on Typography, you can manage the typography settings for text, links,

28
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:58,800
headings, captions and buttons.

29
00:01:58,480 --> 00:02:01,480
A wonderful new feature is that you also now have access to a font library.

30
00:02:04,360 --> 00:02:07,360
Below fonts, we will currently see the fonts that have been added by our theme.

31
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:12,280
But when we click on Manage Fonts, we will be able to install, remove and activate local

32
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:17,760
and Google fonts across your site with any block theme.

33
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:21,960
When you click on Install Fonts, you will be able to install any Google font on your

34
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:27,320
website and click on Upload if you want to upload a font from your computer.

35
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:33,080
Make sure you have the right to use any fonts you are uploading.

36
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:38,280
Below typography, we will see colors.

37
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:40,520
Here, you can also change the colors for different global elements on your site.

38
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:46,880
When we make our way to layout, we will notice you even have control of elements such as

39
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:52,000
padding and block spacing.

40
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:56,040
If you look down further below, you also have the option to customize the appearance of

41
00:02:57,080 --> 00:03:00,080
specific blocks for your whole site.

42
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:03,000
To see how these blocks will change if you edit them, go to your site's Style Book.

43
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:08,080
You will notice there is a little eye at the top.

44
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:11,960
The Style Book allows a user to preview every block that can be inserted into your site.

45
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:18,000
It gives you or provides you an at a glance preview of how global styles will affect any

46
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:23,720
blocks displayed without the user inserting those blocks into a template.

47
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:28,840
It is also important to note that a block's styling can be adjusted within the Style Book.

48
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:34,200
So let's update the Buttons block for example.

49
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:37,920
Let's change the background color and then change the letter case to upper case.

50
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:51,240
If you like what you see, you can go ahead and click Save.

51
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:55,440
Please also note that if you change an individual block in your Style Book, it takes precedence

52
00:03:57,080 --> 00:04:00,080
over the global styles you've set.

53
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:05,840
While we are here, we also need to talk about style revisions.

54
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:08,840
So let's go ahead and click on Style Revisions next to the Style Book icon.

55
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:13,680
Style revisions will open up when you're in the Style Book or when you are editing a template.

56
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:18,040
The styles revisions feature adds a visual way to browse changes to your styles over time

57
00:04:19,960 --> 00:04:22,960
and you can easily revert to a previous stage if you find a style you prefer or want to

58
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:27,320
revert back to a previous version.

59
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:29,680
You merely have to select the version and then click on Apply.

60
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:34,720
In this example, I am editing a template and will follow the same process.

61
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:38,760
I will open up style revisions, select a previous style and then click on Apply to revert back.

62
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:48,000
When you click on the three vertical dots next to styles, you will be able to reset

63
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:53,760
styles as well as add additional CSS.

64
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Below styles, we can go to pages and create and publish pages from here.

65
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:05,200
To add a new page, click on the plus icon next to pages and create a draft.

66
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:10,400
But you can also of course create a new page when you are in your Dashboard or WP Admin.

67
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:16,160
Next, let's open up one of our existing pages, my About Page.

68
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:20,960
When you open a page, it is important to remember to add content to the Content block.

69
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:26,040
To put it another way, the Content block is the house or the container for all your

70
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:29,920
content.

71
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:31,080
The second thing to remember is that you can't customize your header and footer when

72
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:34,880
editing a page.

73
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:36,440
That's all part of managing templates.

74
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:38,600
If you click on the header, you'll get a message that says 'Edit your template to edit

75
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:42,720
this block.'

76
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:44,160
If you want to modify the template that has been assigned to this page, you can click

77
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:48,040
on Edit Template.

78
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:49,800
This will take you to your page template in this example.

79
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:53,000
And here you can modify your header and your footer.

80
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:56,720
You will not be able to add content to a template.

81
00:05:57,120 --> 00:06:00,120
Content of course gets added to posts and pages.

82
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:03,440
The Content block is merely a placeholder in this context.

83
00:06:04,680 --> 00:06:07,680
This brings us to our next topic, namely templates.

84
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:11,000
Templates provide the structure for how your content is displayed.

85
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:14,680
When you select templates, you will notice a range of templates that come with your theme,

86
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:19,480
built-in templates.

87
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:20,800
For example, the page template that displays a single page, the index template that is a

88
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:26,680
fallback template, or the single post template that displays the layout of single posts.

89
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:32,920
And right at the bottom, we will see any custom templates.

90
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:36,840
When you click on the plus icon next to templates, you can add a variety of new templates, even

91
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:42,400
a custom template that can be applied to any post or page.

92
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:45,720
Let's open the page template to better understand how a template works.

93
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:50,400
A template provides structure.

94
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:52,440
A template usually includes a header template part and a footer template part.

95
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:57,520
And the Post Content block pulls in the content from the page or post assigned to the template.

96
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:03,880
So a template is only used to modify the layout or design of the page, namely the header, footer,

97
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:10,000
and even sidebar.

98
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:11,720
The Site Editor therefore makes a clear distinction between editing the template and the page.

99
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:17,640
You can modify your header and footer within the template.

100
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:21,520
One of the options you also have is to click on the three vertical dots and select Replace

101
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:26,360
Header.

102
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:27,360
Then you can replace your current header with one of your existing header template parts

103
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:31,400
or header patterns that come with your theme.

104
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:36,520
Another option you have is to select your header and then click on Edit.

105
00:07:37,160 --> 00:07:40,160
This will allow you to modify your header or footer within template editing mode without

106
00:07:41,420 --> 00:07:44,420
any other distractions.

107
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:46,880
To assign a new template to a page or post, open the relevant piece of content, in this

108
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:52,000
case my About Page, and then in your sidebar settings on the right.

109
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:57,480
Next to template, click on the name of the template, select Swap Template, and then you

110
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:04,840
can choose a custom template to assign to your page or post.

111
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:10,760
It is also worth mentioning that when you click on Manage all templates and then select

112
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:15,680
Bulk Edit, you will be able to explore and filter through your templates via table view

113
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:21,960
or grid view.

114
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:24,120
And when you select Bulk Edit again, there are more filtering options.

115
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:28,880
Please note, you can explore and filter pages and template parts in exactly the same way.

116
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:35,440
Finally, let's talk about patterns.

117
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:40,480
At the top, you will be able to view all the available patterns.

118
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:44,960
When you select My Patterns, you can create and manage your own custom synced and non-synced

119
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:50,600
patterns.

120
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:51,600
Below My Patterns, we can view all our custom patterns as well as patterns that come with

121
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:56,600
our theme in their relevant categories.

122
00:08:57,680 --> 00:09:00,680
And below Template Parts, we can also create and manage our header, footer and general

123
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:06,000
template parts.

124
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:07,960
Template parts are essentially patterns.

125
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:10,760
They are synced reusable components that can be used across your site.

126
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:15,960
Let's start with My Patterns.

127
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:18,280
To create your own custom pattern, click on the Inserter next to patterns and then select

128
00:09:20,860 --> 00:09:23,860
Create Ppattern.

129
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:25,640
After naming it, you can select to add it to relevant category and then decide to sync

130
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:34,800
or not sync your pattern.

131
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:36,960
A synced pattern will sync across your entire site and that means if you make a change to

132
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:42,920
your pattern in one place, it will update anywhere it is used.

133
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:47,360
You can also toggle this off if you prefer to have a non-synced pattern.

134
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:53,480
Non-synced patterns are just regular patterns that can be edited independently.

135
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:59,760
When you return to your custom pattern area, you will notice that synced patterns have a

136
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:04,360
purple icon and non-synced patterns don't.

137
00:10:05,680 --> 00:10:08,680
Next you will notice that the patterns that come with your theme are locked and you are

138
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:12,840
therefore not able to edit them.

139
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:17,080
But when you click on the three vertical dots below a pattern, you will be able to copy

140
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:22,360
it to your my patterns area.

141
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:24,920
At the bottom, we can also create and manage our header, footer and general template parts.

142
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:31,440
You have two options here.

143
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:33,200
You can create custom headers and footers or customize template part patterns that come

144
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:38,520
with your theme.

145
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:39,680
To create your own template part, click on the plus icon at the top next to patterns

146
00:10:42,280 --> 00:10:45,280
and select Create a template part.

147
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:48,080
When you add a new template part, you have an option between general header and footer

148
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:52,240
template parts.

149
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:53,920
General template parts are not tied to any particular area and remember to give them

150
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:58,200
a descriptive name.

151
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:01,240
When you open up a template part from here, you will be able to modify and edit your template

152
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:07,560
part in template editing mode without any distractions.

153
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:11,520
Or, you can open up the relevant template and in this case, my custom template and then

154
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:19,280
you can modify your header or footer template part from within the template.

155
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:24,320
And as shown earlier on, you can easily replace one of your headers or footers with a pattern

156
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:31,440
or an existing template part from the library.

157
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:35,800
To end off, I also want to highlight an extremely helpful feature called the Command palette

158
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:40,560
that will save you loads of time and help you move around your Site Editor more effectively.

159
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:45,800
The command palette allows you to swiftly complete tasks and navigate within the Site

160
00:11:47,680 --> 00:11:50,680
Editor.

161
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:52,120
You can for example type in 'New' to create a page or template or just the name of the

162
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:58,560
area where you want to go.

163
00:11:57,720 --> 00:12:00,720
For example, pattern to manage all my patterns.

164
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:07,800
You can access the command palette by using the shortcut command+k on Mac or control+k

165
00:12:09,920 --> 00:12:12,920
on Windows.

166
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:15,120
You will also find it in the site view sidebar by clicking on the search icon.

167
00:12:21,560 --> 00:12:24,560
Or you can merely click on the title bar.

168
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:29,480
And that is our brief overview of what you are able to achieve using the Site Editor.

